" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uspikescafe.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SpikesCafe</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.spikescafe.com/shell.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Gamera <img src=http://contest.polykarbon.com/badge1.gif></span><br> <font color=#336699>(2/9/02 10:10:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=649.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.spikescafe.com/spikes/jedi.gif height=151 width=100></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: starting out</span><hr size=1> Starting out with hiragana is the norm. However, I find katakana is a little more useful in trying to read Japanese websites, because I don't have the vocabulary or kanjii knowledge to read much else. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>But yeah. Start with hiragana, get a good feel for writing and reading it, and katakana will be easier to pick up. <p><img src="http://www.spikescafe.com/shellt.gif"> <a href="http://www.spikescafe.com/">Spike the Jedi</a> (Uses the Force thanks to wantsomepie)<BR><table width=464 height=64 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td><img src="http://www.spikescafe.com/sig/top.gif"><br><img src="http://www.spikescafe.com/sig/1.gif"><a href="http://www.7hat.com/posting/"><img src="http://www.spikescafe.com/sig/2.gif" border=0></a><img src="http://www.spikescafe.com/sig/3.gif"><a href="http://www.spikescafe.com/crit/crit.htm"><img src="http://www.spikescafe.com/sig/4.gif" border=0></a><img src="http://www.spikescafe.com/sig/5.gif"><ahref="http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm27"target="_newbrow"><img src="http://www.spikescafe.com/sig/